JDBC - Java DataBase Connectivity

steps to the connectivity
1) import the package (java.sql.*)
2) load & register the driver
3) establish the connection
4) create the statement
5) execute the Query
6) process the result
7) close

In SQL we have,
Data Definition Language(DDL) - whenever you create or modify the structure of the database or table
Data Manipulation Language(DML) - whenever you insert, delete and modifying data in a database
Data Query Language(DQL) - whenever you want to query to fetching the value, SELECT: It is used to retrieve data from the database.
Data Control Language(DCL) - control access to data stored in a database. DCL includes commands such as GRANT and REVOKE which mainly deal with the rights, permissions, and other controls of the database system.